<DOC><DOCNO> AP880311-0073 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-03-11-88 0832EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-BRF--Zimbabwe-Drown     03-11 0130</FIRST><SECOND>PM-BRF--Zimbabwe-Drown,0133</SECOND><HEAD>8 Die Crossing Flooded River Near Mozambique</HEAD><DATELINE>HARARE, Zimbabwe (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Eight soldiers guarding the easternfrontier against rebel incursions were drowned while crossing aflood-swollen river during a patrol, it was reported today.   The soldiers of the 61st infantry battalion were drowned in theHonde River that cuts through the eastern highlands near the borderwith Mozambique, according to a Defense Ministry statementpublished by the Herald newspaper.   The victims were a sergeant, three corporals and four privates,the statement said. It gave no other details.   Several battalions of Zimbabwe troops are stationed along the750-mile border following raids by rebels of the MozambiqueNational Resistance. The guerrillas have killed more than 40villagers, abducted scores of others, looted shops and houses anddestroyed government vehicles.  </TEXT></DOC>